  "prompt": "Some companies use sports sponsorship as a way to advertise themselves. Is this a benefit or a risk to the company?",
  "prompt_jp": "スポーツのスポンサーになるのは企業にとって利益かリスクか（リスク面を論じる）。",
  "outline_jp": [
    "譲歩: 一方でリスクもある",
    "理由: 選手の不祥事に巻き込まれる",
    "例: 飲酒運転で悪評・企業の悪夢",
    "結論: 費用不足でも最善を望みリスクに備える"
  ],
  "model_answer": [
    "Admittedly, there are certain risks to being a patron of an athlete or team.",
    "First of all, if a player gets involved in a scandal, it will reflect badly on the sponsor.",
    "For example, a golfer once arrested on a drink-driving charge became a nightmare for his sponsor's PR department.",
    "Another possible scenario is that the star could fall ill and be knocked out of a tournament.",
    "On the other hand, sportspeople still need to look for sponsors, and companies are usually happy enough to provide funding for good public relations.",
    "In conclusion, firms know they are running a risk, yet they prepare for the worst and hope for the best."
  ],
